Merged Video
Description
This webpage demonstrates the merging of two videos using the Video.js library. It provides a simple interface with a video player that switches between two video sources when one video ends, creating a looping effect.

Preview
Insert a screenshot or provide a live link to your webpage here.

Getting Started
To view this webpage, simply open the index.html file in a web browser. Ensure an internet connection to load the Video.js library from the content delivery network (CDN).

Usage
Open the index.html file in a web browser.
The page will display a video player with controls.
The initial video (vid1.mp4) will play, and when it ends, it will switch to the second video (vid2.mp4).
The switching between videos will continue in a loop.
Customization
Feel free to customize the content of the webpage as needed. You can replace the video files (vid1.mp4 and vid2.mp4) and update the references accordingly.

Dependencies
Video.js - Version 7.14.3
